PN,39902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F399A1778753278
OL,3,CPlotting Southport-style mass casualty
OL,4,Cattacks to become criminal offence
OL,6,FMeasures under the National Security
OL,7,FBill will "criminalise planning a mass
OL,8,Fcasualty attack, closing a clear gap
OL,9,Fin the current law by capturing cases
OL,10,Fwhere a lone individual undertakes
OL,11,Fpreparatory steps towards a mass
OL,12,Fcasualty attack without an ideological
OL,13,Fmotive".
OL,15,FThe King said the Government "will
OL,16,Frespond to the horrific attack in
OL,17,FSouthport with measures to protect the
OL,18,FBritish people from extreme violence,
OL,19,Fand honour the victims, the injured
OL,20,Fand their families".
OL,26,@oD@KOUuD@GO]wD@^OU|D@SO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/7
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
